cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "SemiHS-Bench: A Semiconductor Benchmark for HS6 Classification from Sparse ERP-Style Text"
message: "If you use this benchmark, dataset, or code, please cite the paper below."
type: dataset
version: "2.0.0"
date-released: "2026-06-08"
url: "https://github.com/cti-iel/SemiHS-Bench"
repository-code: "https://github.com/cti-iel/SemiHS-Bench"
license: CC-BY-SA-4.0
abstract: >
  SemiHS-Bench is a benchmark for six-digit Harmonized System (HS6) tariff
  classification of semiconductor supply-chain products from real ERP-style
  text. Each product is represented through controlled input tiers derived from
  the same observation, with labels grounded in a held-out multilingual corpus
  of customs rulings (EBTI, CROSS, and Japan Customs). The benchmark exposes
  two evaluation modes: a constrained 4-way ranking with a 25% random baseline,
  and an open ranking against the in-scope HS6 taxonomy. It ships two matched
  900-record splits (eval and train, 1,800 records total) with identical HS6
  coverage across 38 HS4 families / 73 HS6 codes, and a reference corpus of
  889 customs rulings.
keywords:
  - HS code classification
  - tariff classification
  - LLM benchmark
  - information retrieval
  - supply chain intelligence
  - trade compliance
  - semiconductor
